Package comp3111.covid

Class TableController

java.lang.Object
comp3111.covid.TableController
Direct Known Subclasses:
TableAController, TableBController, TableCController
public abstract class TableController
extends java.lang.Object
A general, abstract controller class that handles the initializations of UI elements within a Tab, and the updating of table.

    • initializeComponents

      protected abstract void initializeComponents​(Controller controller)
      An abstract initializer that takes in only one controller, this is created for derived classes to inherit from. In particular, within the body, the other initializer with many more arguments can be called. This offers the advantage that wherever this version of initializeComponents is called, only 1 argument is needed, where the logic for initializing all other components (by calling the other version of initializeComponents) can be contained within the derived class.
      Parameters:
      controller -

    • initializeComponents

      public void initializeComponents​(Controller controller, TableDataAnalysis tableDataAnalysis, TableViewInternal tableViewInternal, javafx.scene.control.Button buttonCSVExport, javafx.scene.control.DatePicker datePicker, org.controlsfx.control.CheckComboBox<java.lang.String> dropDownMenu, javafx.scene.control.Label tableTitle, javafx.scene.control.TableView tableView)
      Initializer for all components within a Table Tab.
      Parameters:
      controller - the main controller
      tableDataAnalysis - the tableDataAnalysis
      tableViewInternal - the tableViewInternal
      buttonCSVExport - the button for exporting table to csv
      datePicker - the datePicker, from which a user selects a date
      dropDownMenu - the dropDownMenu, from which a user selects a country
      tableTitle - the table title
      tableView - the table being displayed

    • updateTable

      protected void updateTable​(javafx.event.ActionEvent e)
      The method that updates tableViewInternal to be displayed, invoked whenever there is a change in selected date and list of countries. Update takes place only when there are both a selected date, and a non-empty list of countries.
      Parameters:
      e - the event

    • getTableData

      protected abstract java.util.List<java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Object>> getTableData()
      An abstract method that returns table data, in the form of a List of Maps. Invoked when there is an update to table. Each Map is in the format: 
                      {
                        "Country": name_of_country,
                        column1: query1_value,
                        column2: query2_value
                }
      Returns:
      Returns table data in the form of a List of Maps

    • loadTable

      protected abstract void loadTable()
      An abstract method that loads the table. Invoked when there is an update to table.
